{"title":"Let’s Give Hope Cyclery Some Hope","link":"https://theradavist.com/help-hope-cyclery/","date":1688856710000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202242.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202242.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202242.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202242.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202242.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202242.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202242.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202242.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Hope Cyclery, run by our good friends Jarrod and David, in Johnstown, PA, recently had their shop broken into. Everyone knows it’s not easy being an independent bike shop these days, yet Hope Cyclery has been building community and increasing cycling awareness in an area that is struggling.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202245.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202245.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202245.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202245.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202245.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202245.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202245.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-202245.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-20227.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-20227.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-20227.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-20227.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-20227.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-20227.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-20227.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Higher-Ground-20227.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Hope Cyclery has brought cycling tourism to local businesses through the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2022-higher-ground-hope-cyclery/\" target=\"_blank\">Higher Ground event</a> and increased awareness of outdoor recreation potential in this post-steel industry setting.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2352\" height=\"1568\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" alt srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?w=2352&amp;quality=75 2352w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/07/Screenshot-2023-07-08-at-4.34.35-PM.png?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Today, they were broken into and lost inventory while leading a group ride. Already on a shoestring budget, this might break them. We know money is tight right now, but if you’ve been wanting a new, custom build, <a href=\"https://hopecyclery.com/products/buy-a-bike-from-hope?_pos=1&amp;_sid=7854d69a8&amp;_ss=r\" target=\"_blank\">Hope has a deposit web page set up to take deposits.</a> Or you can browse <a href=\"https://hopecyclery.com/collections/all?sort_by=price-ascending\" target=\"_blank\">their in-stock inventory</a>. If you’re curious about what kind of builds Hope offers and what Jarrod has done for The Radavist over the years, check out our Related Archives below.</p>\n<p>Let’s give them some love on their <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/hopecyclery/\" target=\"_blank\">Instagram</a> too!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/help-hope-cyclery/\">Let’s Give Hope Cyclery Some Hope</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"f07c4b76f94f838daf35f864ffdb9fe64970af6c1863a1f70a11038993b86aa1","category":"Cycling"}